-- Bank of Korea’s Kim Declines to Comment on Foreign Exchange Plan
-- B y   C h o n g   P o o i   K o o n
-- 2012-05-14T11:27:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-14/bank-of-korea-s-kim-declines-to-comment-on-foreign-exchange-plan.html
Bank of Korea Governor Kim Choong Soo
declined to comment on the country’s foreign exchange policy to
reporters in  Kuala Lumpur  today.  “We don’t make it public on what we will do regarding our
foreign exchange policy,” Kim said at a press conference in
Malaysia today. “Japan may have a different approach but we
take a very conservative approach. We don’t intend to hint on
any actions.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chong Pooi Koon in Kuala Lumpur at 
 pchong17@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
